    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop the closure of the Public Switched Telephone Network",
        "additional_details": "The PSTN works with a simple corded phone into a landline, & continues to work even when a powercut occurs. Digital broadband & Voice over Internet Protocol services are often disrupted.\r\n \r\nDuring a powercut, with mobile reception poor due to severe weather conditions, the PSTN can still work fine, providing a communication option for elderly and vulnerable people to stay in contact with friends and family.\r\n \r\nDigital systems often won't work, and mobiles can be out of credit/charge.",
        "background": "Stop the closure of the Public Switched Telephone Network, prioritising safety of elderly and vulnerable people.",
